-- Russia Equity Movers: Mail.Ru, Mobile TeleSystems, Rosneft
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-05-21T15:45:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-21/russia-equity-movers-gazprom-mobile-telesystems-rosneft.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose 2.1
percent to 1,298.42 by the close in Moscow.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Gazprom (GAZP RX) rose 2.6 percent to 142.02 rubles,
snapping five days of declines and adding the most since April
27. Troika Dialog raised Russia’s gas export monopoly to buy
from hold, citing low valuations.  Mail.ru (MAIL)   fell 9.1 percent to $33.40 by 3:40 p.m.
in  London , the most since Dec. 6. The largest Russian-language
 Internet company  and an investor in Facebook Inc. fell as the
social networking site slid below its $38 initial offer price.  OAO Mobile TeleSystems (MTSS RX) added 1.4 percent to
208.90 rubles, the most since May 2. Russia’s biggest mobile
operator advanced after first-quarter profit rose 59 percent
from a year earlier as it cut financing costs and benefited from
a stronger ruble.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX) fell 1.4 percent to 194.99 rubles,
its lowest level since May 8. Russia’s biggest oil producer
dropped as MSCI Inc. canceled a decision to increase the stock’s
weighting in its Russia Index.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
